[4] Suspected, monitored, quarantined, prevention

16 Mar 2015 Denmark: 3 Danish health workers were sent home from Sierra Leone on suspicions of being infected with the deadly Ebola virus.
http://sputniknews.com/europe/20150316/1019563870.html#ixzz3UaAlkTIN
[Workers were in contact with an American Ebola patient in Sierra Leone and were returned back home Sun 15 Mar 2015. Initial exam was negative for Ebola symptoms; see RFI in report [2] above.]

16 Mar 2015: Denmark extends Ebola efforts in Sierra Leone
http://cphpost.dk/news/denmark-extends-ebola-efforts-in-sierra-Leone.13031.html
[The government has decided to extend until mid-June 2015 its Ebola treatment efforts in Port Loko, Sierra Leone]

17 Mar 2015 Gambia: WHO boosts Health Ministry's Ebola preparedness
http://allafrica.com/stories/201503171150.html?viewall=1
[World Health Organization, with support from the British Embassy, recently donated medical equipment to the Ministry of Health in Banjul, Gambia to help prevent Ebola]

17 Mar 2015 Guinea: finalizes plan to eradicate Ebola by 15 April 2015
http://www.inform.kz/eng/article/2756251
[Guinea's authorities in charge of eradication of the Ebola epidemic are finalizing an interim plan to end the epidemic by 15 Apr 2015, an official source has said. This new plan follows the initial plan called "Zero Ebola in 60 days," which elapsed on 10 Mar 2015, and failed to yield the desired results]

16 Mar 2015 Japan: Suspected Ebola patient tests negative in Japan
http://www.economylead.com/international/suspected-ebola-patient-tests-negative-in-japan-62405
[Non-Japanese national who returned to Tokyo from Liberia has tested negative for the Ebola virus after developing a fever on Sun night [15 Mar 2015], the health ministry said on Mon, 16 Mar 2015]

16 Mar 2015 Liberia: As Ebola slows, social life ramps up
http://www.voanews.com/content/as-ebola-slows-social-life-ramps-up-in-liberia/2681898.html
[Liberians have returned to churches, popular beaches and nightclubs; "cramming into public buses and cabs, without worry"]

16 Mar 2015 New Zealand: Confirmed negative Ebola test for health worker
http://www.scoop.co.nz/stories/PA1503/S00232/confirmed-negative-ebola-test-for-health-worker.htm

16 Mar 2015 Sierra Leone: China Donates 40 Ambulances to Boost Fight Against Ebola
http://allafrica.com/stories/201503160896.html?viewall=1

16 Mar 2015 Sierra Leone: NRA sustains Ebola relief efforts
http://allafrica.com/stories/201503170998.html?viewall=1
[National Revenue Authority (NRA) is maintaining its education and relief efforts in combating the Ebola virus. For the past 2 weeks they have donated assorted food items including rice, sugar, oil, butter and sardines. The Authority has selected Port Loko and Bombali districts for special consideration due to new cases of Ebola emerging there]

17 Mar 2015 Sierra Leone: Ebola-self-quarantined Sierra Leone VP requests US asylum as 11 exposed Americans fly home
http://www.breitbart.com/national-security/2015/03/16/ebola-quarantined-sierra-leone-vp-requests-us-asylum-as-11-americans-flown-home/
[Vice-president Sam-Sumana requested asylum at the United States Embassy]

17 Mar 2015 Sierra Leone: President Koroma admonishes Bombali
http://allafrica.com/stories/201503171229.html
[The President rebuked his home district for not complying with the bylaws and regulations meant to break the chain of transmission of the disease, saying that if they had fully complied with the laws they wouldn't have lagged behind so far in the fight to end the epidemic. He admonished the people of Bombali to take ownership and responsibility of the fight against Ebola, to strengthen the checkpoints, and to halt the unabated cultural and traditional practices by the people]

17 Mar 2015 UK: Hundreds sign petition urging probe into Scots Ebola nurse be halted
http://news.stv.tv/west-central/314114-hundreds-sign-petition-urging-probe-into-scots-ebola-nurse-be-axed/
[She is alleged to have covered up feeling unwell on return to the UK]

16 Mar 2015 UK: Ebola: 7th British health worker sent home
http://www.bbc.com/news/health-31908301
[A 7th health-care worker (from the same facility where the USA HC-worker contracted Ebola) was flown back to the UK following suspected Ebola contact. Patient is asymptomatic, has been evaluated at Royal Victoria Infirmary and discharged, under close observation. 2 other UK HC-workers remain at Royal Free Hospital: 1 was diagnosed with Ebola while in Sierra Leone and flown back to the UK on an RAF plane on 12 Mar 2015; the other sustained a needlestick injury while caring for an Ebola patient in Sierra Leone]

USA
----

16 Mar 2015 USA: American who contracted Ebola now in critical condition
http://www.wcvb.com/health/american-who-contracted-ebola-now-in-critical-condition/31824826
[According to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, besides the patient at NIH, there are 11 other Partners in Health workers being brought to the USA for monitoring, including 4 going to Atlanta to be near Emory University Hospital, 1 of whom arrived on Fri 13 Mar 2015. On 14 Mar 2015, 4 health-care workers arrived at the Nebraska Medical Center in Omaha, and 3 arrived in the Washington area on Sun 15 Mar 2015 to be near the NIH campus in Bethesda. Those workers have no Ebola symptoms but may have been exposed.]

16 Mar 2015 USA: Health care worker being monitored for Ebola in Omaha moved to biocontainment unit
http://www.ketv.com/news/health-care-worker-being-monitored-for-ebola-in-omaha-moved-to-biocontainment-unit/31825222
[1 of the 4 health-care workers being treated in Omaha "out of an abundance of caution" has not tested Ebola-positive, but has had a change of symptoms; some of those symptoms have resolved. A 5th person who was part of the initial exposure is expected to arrive at the Nebraska Medical Center for monitoring on Mon, 16 Mar 2015]

17 Mar 2015: U.S., Taiwan to set up training center to combat Ebola spread
http://focustaiwan.tw/news/aipl/201503170019.aspx
[Scheduled to open 18 Mar 2015, the training center will be in the southern city of Tainan. Target goal will be to train more medical workers in the Asian-Pacific region; focus is on Ebola. The program will take place at a disease control and prevention facility in Tainan. The USA has already trained some Taiwanese personnel to be seed instructors for the program, which will include 18 trainees and instructors]

17 Mar 2015: 4 more aid workers flown back to US for Ebola monitoring
http://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/stories/U/US_EBOLA_AMERICAN_PATIENT?SITE=AP&SECTION=HOME&TEMPLATE=DEFAULT&CTIME=2015-03-17-13-25-29
[Total of 16 health-care workers flown from Sierra Leone back to the USA: 1 was the index HC worker who tested positive for Ebola on 10 Mar 2015; 15 possibly made physical contact with the index HC worker. The 15 HC workers are staying near the Maryland hospital, or hospitals in Atlanta and Omaha, which have special isolation units in case the HC workers become ill.]

Non-governmental organizations
-----------------------------------------
16 Mar 2015: Partners in Health plans to stay in West Africa even as one of its workers is stricken with Ebola
http://www.bostonglobe.com/metro/2015/03/16/partners-health-plans-stay-west-africa-even-one-its-workers-stricken-with-ebola/zhgRrNHiuBj6gkbavmatZN/story.html
[PIH plans to broaden the foothold it established during the Ebola outbreak in Sierra Leone and Liberia. PIH is not an emergency-response agency; its specialty is training and empowering the local population to improve care. PIH has 2000 employees at work in West Africa, mostly local residents, including hundreds of Ebola survivors. PIH has more than 150 American staff members in Liberia and Sierra Leone. Many of them are clinicians who work for 5-week stints. PIH raised about USD 30 million for its Ebola work, the majority of which is coming from the USA and United Kingdom governments. That money is designated for Ebola. PIH is now looking to its donors (governments, foundations, individuals) to pay for PIH's ongoing efforts]

17 Mar 2015 Save the Children: 28 nations next high-risk Ebola zones
http://allafrica.com/stories/201503171739.html?viewall=1

16 Mar 2015 UNICEF: 1 out of 5 Ebola infections hits a child
http://www.unicef.org/emergencies/ebola/files/EbolaReport.pdf

Vaccine
---------------
16 Mar 2015: Ebola booster vaccine trial to combine GSK, Emergent Bio shots
http://www.reuters.com/article/2015/03/16/health-ebola-vaccine-idUSL6N0WI24Z20150316?rpc=401
[Modified vaccinia Ankara (MVA) Ebola Zaire vaccine to be used in an initial Phase I clinical study by researchers at the University of Oxford]

17 Mar 2015 Russia: Fear Ebola no more -- Russia starts testing 4 Ebola vaccines on primates
http://sputniknews.com/society/20150317/1019607039.html#ixzz3UfB3kWCj
[4 Ebola virus vaccines developed by Russian scientists are being tested on primates]

Funding
-----------
15 Mar 2015 Liberia: Chinese provides USD 35 000 funding for Ebola orphans and survivors
http://allafrica.com/stories/201503171044.html?viewall=1
[Each Ebola survivor received USD 300, one bag of rice and a gallon of vegetable oil; USD 10 000 will be used to construct a safe house for orphans, and to provide "stationaries," one bag of rice and a gallon of vegetable oil. Is the stationery for schoolwork? - Mod.JW]

17 Mar 2015 Jamaica: Health Ministry spends JD 22 million on Ebola preparedness
http://www.jamaicaobserver.com/news/Health-Ministry-spends-J-22m-on-Ebola-preparedness
[Funds spent are JD 22 million (USD 191 088) since 14 Oct 2015 on public education and communication in the preparedness and response phase of the Ebola Integrated Response Strategy]

